text = "July 13th
I’m worried. At first I thought it was just a coping mechanism for Lilian after we heard about the bad news. So I didn't mention anything. But it’s been months since she found out that she is infertile and she still talks to that imaginary child. It’s always ‘Gerald, Roseline wants to go out to play’ or ‘Gerald, Roseline is sleeping so be quiet.’ Sometimes it can be straight up terrifying. Just last night I heard her ‘cooing Roseline’ back to sleep. I went to the room where the sound was coming from and I saw her on a rocking chair with her hand curled up as if cradling a baby. If things continue this way I might need to seek professional help.
"
